Package com.iontrading.mkv

Class MkvE2ETickData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iontrading.mkv.MkvTickData
      • com.iontrading.mkv.MkvE2ETickData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMkvTickData
    @Keep
@KeepPublicClassMembers
public class MkvE2ETickData
extends MkvTickData
    This class cares about collecting tick by tick measures and computing their distribution into time buckets.
    The usage of this class is to repeatedly add tick by tick measures using the add() method and then obtain the distribution or the related percentiles through the appropriated calls.
    The class can also be used to report the distribution of the collected ticks as well as their percentiles.

    The buckets have a configurable number of decimal places that can be specified when creating a new instance of the class.
    By default, no decimal places are used to fill the buckets.

    For each different instance registered to the MkvTickDataCollector, a periodic trace is added to the STATISTICS log every seconds, reporting the information about the tick value distribution.

    See Also:
    MkvTickDataCollector
